instance virtual_to_physical_interaction : DTDFVocab:VirtualToPhysical [
    base:desc "Control commands originating from the User Interface FE (e.g., acceleration, brake, steering requests) are routed through the Digital Twin’s Actuation FE components (Motor Actuation FE and Steering Servo Actuation FE) using the ROS2 network. Prior to transmission, the Data Translation component re‑serialises the commands, ensuring consistent message format and units. The actuation commands are then sent to the physical actuators over the Wi‑Fi network with UDP transport. Feedback of updated vehicle state information returned by the Vehicle State FE provides confirmation of command execution, allowing the Digital Twin to reconcile command status with the real‑world response."
